This paper is about building dialog systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also incorporates multimodal information, including acoustic and dialogic information, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper uses supervised and reinforcement learning, which are common techniques in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
